==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prester
<hw>Pres"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/,
from <?/ to kindle or burn, and <?/ to blow up, swell out by
blowing.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A meteor or exhalation formerly
supposed to be thrown from the clouds with such violence that by
collision it is set on fire.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>One of the veins of the neck when
swollen with anger or other excitement.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prester</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prester
<hw>Pres"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>prestre</ets>. See
<er>Priest</er>.]</ety> <def>A priest or presbyter; <as>as,
<ex>Prester</ex> John</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presternum</ent>⟦br⟧
